{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":54664,"name":"Graham Morrison","username":"degville","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/forum.snapcraft.io/degville/{size}/2021_2.png","created_at":"2019-09-06T10:52:30.449Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe \u003ccode\u003eaudio-record\u003c/code\u003e interface allows an application to access your audio recording hardware, such as a microphone, via your system’s audio service, such as PulseAudio. It’s disabled by default.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis interface is a companion interface to the \u003ca href=\"/t/the-audio-playback-interface/13089\"\u003eaudio-playback\u003c/a\u003e interface, and is not intended to be used without it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"heading--example\"\u003eExample\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe brilliant \u003ca href=\"https://snapcraft.io/obs-studio\"\u003eOBS Studio\u003c/a\u003e is a good example of an application that needs access to your microphone/audio recording hardware.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-bash\"\u003e$ sudo snap connect obs-studio:audio-record\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"p-notification--positive\"\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"p-notification__response\"\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"p-notification__status\"\u003e\nInterface documentation: \u003c/span\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\nSee \u003ca href=\"/t/interface-management/6154\"\u003eInterface management\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"/t/supported-interfaces/7744\"\u003eSupported interfaces\u003c/a\u003e for further details on how interfaces are used.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003chr\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"heading--dev-details\"\u003eDeveloper details \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAuto-connect\u003c/strong\u003e: no\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe design of this interface is based on the principle that the slot implementation of the audio service, such as \u003ca href=\"/t/the-pulseaudio-interface/7906\"\u003ePulseAudio\u003c/a\u003e, queries whether its audio-record slot is connected, leaving the audio service to mediate recording if it is.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOn systems with snapd integration, PulseAudio’s mediation is limited and will only verify that the \u003cem\u003esnap\u003c/em\u003e is connected to \u003ccode\u003eaudio-record\u003c/code\u003e and not if the specific snap command plugs the interface.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eCode examples\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMumble is a voice chat platform and a good example of an application using audio-record. Its snapcraft.yaml can be found here:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/snapcrafters/mumble/blob/b5f1644a72a14cacd17b862cd0265d21d8ce604a/snap/snapcraft.yaml#L21\"\u003ehttps://github.com/snapcrafters/mumble/blob/master/snap/snapcraft.yaml\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe source code for this interface is in the \u003cem\u003esnapd\u003c/em\u003e repository:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/snapcore/snapd/blob/master/interfaces/builtin/audio_record.go\"\u003ehttps://github.com/snapcore/snapd/blob/master/interfaces/builtin/audio_record.go\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2021-07-15T09:04:32.513Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":126,"reads":20,"readers_count":19,"score":649.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":13090,"topic_slug":"the-audio-record-interface","display_username":"Graham Morrison","primary_group_name":null,"primary_group_flair_url":null,"primary_group_flair_bg_color":null,"primary_group_flair_color":null,"version":6,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/the-audio-playback-interface/13089","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"The audio-playback interface","clicks":13},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/interface-management/6154","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Interface management","clicks":8},{"url":"https://github.com/snapcrafters/mumble/blob/b5f1644a72a14cacd17b862cd0265d21d8ce604a/snap/snapcraft.yaml#L21","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"mumble/snapcraft.yaml at b5f1644a72a14cacd17b862cd0265d21d8ce604a · snapcrafters/mumble · GitHub","clicks":6},{"url":"https://snapcraft.io/obs-studio","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Install OBS Studio on Linux | Snap Store","clicks":6},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/the-pulseaudio-interface/7906","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"The pulseaudio interface","clicks":6},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/supported-interfaces/7744","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Supported interfaces","clicks":4},{"url":"https://github.com/snapcore/snapd/blob/master/interfaces/builtin/audio_record.go","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"snapd/audio_record.go at master · snapcore/snapd · GitHub","clicks":1},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/upcoming-pulseaudio-interface-deprecation/13418","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Upcoming pulseaudio interface deprecation","clicks":3},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/snap-documentation/11127/12","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Snap documentation","clicks":1},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/the-alsa-interface/7766","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"The alsa interface","clicks":0},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/snap-documentation/11127","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Snap documentation","clicks":0},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/the-desktop-interfaces/2042","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"The desktop interfaces","clicks":0},{"url":"https://forum.snapcraft.io/t/snapcraft-checklist/10926","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Snapcraft checklist","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":true,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":2772,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view